# Build Observer Self-Maintenance

## Step

Standing call (Joel, 2026-07-14): "observer should occasionally systems
check itself, garden open panes, reflect on its state in the system for
observation." Add a periodic self-maintenance behavior to the observer
family (a tick step or its own cadence, e.g. every Nth tick):

- **Systems check**: family integrity (dispatcher alive on current
  release, tick log healthy, dedupe state sane, telemetry watch state
  fresh, unpublished observation backlog size).
- **Pane gardening**: close/adopt stray panes in the observer herdr
  session (dead workers, too-small retries, stale labels) — the
  2026-07-14 dispatcher too-small loop and w2/w3 sprawl are the case
  studies; supervisor-owned, deterministic, receipts logged.
- **Self-reflection for observation**: a periodic observation page about
  the observer's own state (pages written, spend, anomalies it raised,
  what it fixed) — the loop observing itself, same schema, same noise
  bar; feeds the masthead and the reflector like everything else.

Constraints: deterministic where possible, pi judgment only behind the
existing schemas; never touch panes outside the observer session; the
self-page respects the noise bar (no daily empty navel-gazing — write
only when there's signal).

## Result (2026-07-14)

Built in `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer` as staged machinery. First live run is steering's.

Receipts:

- Pure self-check functions in `.pi/extensions/observer/lib.ts`: `assembleSelfCheckReport`, `assessFileHealth`.
- Pure pane gardening in `.pi/extensions/observer/lib.ts`: `decideObserverPaneGardening`; protected observer/dispatcher panes are rename-only, never close.
- Self-reflection noise bar + page builder/validator in `.pi/extensions/observer/lib.ts`: `shouldWriteSelfReflection`, `assembleSelfReflectionObservation`, `validateSelfReflectionObservation`.
- Supervisor CLI in `.pi/extensions/observer/self-maintenance.ts`; `--dry-run` reads real state without mutation, `--apply` is for the staged tick script only.
- Staged repo copy of the supervisor script at `bin/observer-tick.sh`, headed as vNext and calling `self_maintenance` before the tick send.
- Tests added in `test/observer.test.ts` for integrity report assembly, protected-pane gardening, noise bar, and validator.
- Verification: `bun test` green, 69 pass.
- Real dry run (read-only) found dispatcher alive on release sha `31f5fc543ed4`, tick/family/dedupe/telemetry/pending state healthy, unpublished backlog `0`, and one warning: `/tmp/observer-context.log` missing. It proposed closing stale pane `w3:pM` and renaming observer/dispatcher labels; no actions were applied.

## Installed (2026-07-15)

Steering installed the staged wiring into production per Joel's standing
call ("the observer session needs to be cleaned up regularly and should
occupy a single tab … all named and consistent and not duplicates or
noops"):

- Manual gardening pass first: closed 4 dead/blank panes (`w4:p1`,
  `w4:pF`, `w4:pG`, `w4:pH`) and 1 finished scheduled worker (`w4:pC`,
  the cold-proof SPAWN — its receipt confirmed HTTP 200 + DM sent),
  collapsing 4 tabs to the single family tab.
- Lesson recorded: `w4:pH` was the LIVE observer mislabeled by its own
  nested subagent (the `HERDR_PANE_ID` inheritance gotcha); the v4
  gardening rename-to-canonical (`👁️ Observer` / `📡 Dispatcher`)
  prevents that disguise recurring. The blank `w4:pG`/tab `w4:t8` came
  from the v3 tick script's `tab create` shape-gap (`result.root_pane`)
  — fixed in the staged copy now installed.
- Install: repo `bin/observer-tick.sh` (at `34a5056`) copied to
  `~/.joelclaw/bin/observer-tick.sh`, headed as v4; LaunchAgent
  `com.joelclaw.observer-tick` unchanged (same path, 1800s interval).
- Supervised v4 run: recreated observer as `w4:pJ` via split from
  dispatcher, self-maintenance `--apply` ran live — gardening applied
  one real fix (dispatcher label drift → `📡 Dispatcher`), noise bar
  said write (gardening acted), self-reflection page validated
  (`2026-07-15-observer-self-reflection`), one honest warning
  (`observer-context` log missing — that LaunchAgent is staged, not
  installed, by design).
- End state verified: ONE family tab `w4:t5`, exactly two panes —
  `👁️ Observer` (`w4:pJ`, working) + `📡 Dispatcher` (`w4:p8`, idle).
- Still staged: the self-reflection observation WRITE path
  (`writePolicy: staged only`) — the page is built and validated each
  run but not yet written to `.brain/observations`.
